Post-Match Reflections: New Zealand captain Kane Williamson: 'The boys did well today. Whatever target you're chasing on that surface is going to be a grind, I'm glad we made it over the line.'

Papua New Guinea captain Assad Vala: 'There's lots of learning we can take away from this game, especially the batting aspect of the game. The other bowlers have been challenging, but we gave our best.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: Both sides already eliminated from Super 8s contention
Others: Trent Boult is working his way his way around the boundary, signing things and posing for photos. It's his last game in the format for New Zealand, and probably his last ever.
